text.section:
The Administration shall issue a salvage certificate:
To an insurance company or its authorized agent that:
Is licensed to insure automobiles in this State;
Acquires a vehicle as the result of a claim settlement; and
Within 10 days after the date of settlement, applies for a salvage certificate as provided in subsection (c) of this section;
To an automotive dismantler and recycler that:
Acquires a salvage vehicle from a source other than an insurance company licensed to insure automobiles in this State;
Acquires a salvage vehicle by a means other than a transfer of a salvage certificate; and
Applies for a salvage certificate as provided in subsection (d) of this section; or
To any other person who:
Acquires or retains ownership of a vehicle that is salvage, as defined in § 11-152 of this article;
Applies for a salvage certificate on a form provided by the Administration; and
Pays a fee established by the Administration.
